Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them
onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{for
potatoes} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @dried rosemary{1%tsp}, @panko
breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs (see
pantry for both amounts), then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per
person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto another baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of
your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the
dressing (see pantry for amount) to a #medium bowl{}.

Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}(if you have any),
then mix together and set the dressing aside.

Quarter, core and thinly slice the @apple{1}(quartered, cored and thinly sliced)
(no need to peel).

When the burgers are cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the
burgers and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted,
~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop them onto a baking tray and
into oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When ready, spread the @BBQ sauce{64%g} over the bun bases and lids. Top the
bases with the cheesy burgers and some @wild rocket{20%g}, then sandwich
shut.

Add the apple and remaining rocket to the dressing and toss to coat.

> TIP: Set aside a little salad for those who'd prefer it without dressing
and toss to coat.

Serve your burgers with the wedges and salad alongside. Enjoy!